Interface CacheElementInfo

All Superinterfaces:
ElementInfoHelperMethods, TypeInfo, TypeInfoHelperMethods, TypeModifiers
All Known Subinterfaces:
CacheArgument, CacheArgumentInfo, CacheArgumentMetadata, CacheField, CacheFieldInfo, CacheFieldMetadata
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractElementInfoImpl
public interface CacheElementInfo
extends TypeModifiers, TypeInfo, ElementInfoHelperMethods

This interface represents common information about Cache concepts like Property definition or Method arguments definitions.

See Also:
CacheField, CacheMethod

getType

CacheClass getType()
                   throws CacheException
Returns the CacheClass corresponding to the type of this essense. Invocation of this method will cause Java client to request loading corresponding class from the Database. Use getTypeName to avoid loading CacheClass.

Returns:
type of the essence represented as CacheClass object.
Throws:
CacheException

getElementType

int getElementType()
                   throws CacheException
This method is meaningful only if the essense is of collection type. In this case it will return the name of the type of elements in the collection.

Specified by:
getElementType in interface TypeInfoHelperMethods
Returns:
integer specifying the type of the element in collection: PERISTENT, SERIAL or DATATYPE as specified by TypeModifiers interface.
Throws:
CacheException
See Also:
TypeModifiers.PERSISTENT, TypeModifiers.SERIAL, TypeModifiers.DATATYPE

getModifiers

int getModifiers()
Returns modifier flags which can be used to determine whether the described essence is literal or object, static or per instance, has default value or not, etc. The CacheModifier class should be used to decode the modifiers.

Returns:
modifiers represented as an int.
See Also:
CacheModifier

getJavaName

java.lang.String getJavaName()
returns Java name of element which may differ from its name, for instance an argument whose name is %arg will have a Java name of _name, and an argument whose name is class will have a Java name of _class

Returns:
Name of corresponding Java element represented as String.
